Global Dictionary Gap Solution

	Philosophy

		-
			When attempting to express an idea in a given language for which there is no
			appropriate term, words should be sourced from the global dictionary to supplement the
			gap.
		-

	Principles

		Esperanto

			-
				One's first resort in sourcing words from the global dictionary with which to
				supplement a given language should be to source said words from Esperanto.
